description:
PROBLEM STATEMENT ONLY — capture for a deliberate design session later; do NOT pre-solution this.

Operations (contract-fleet, gate/construction drain, worker-rebalancer, factory, scout, frontier-expansion, stocker) independently contend for ships from a shared idle pool, repeatedly claiming and releasing them per-tick (e.g. construction releaseClaims every drain tick; contract idle_arb grabs whatever is unclaimed). Hulls never settle — they oscillate between operations. That tug-of-war is the shared root behind several symptoms seen this session:
- gate-FAB starvation from contract poaching un-dedicated gate haulers (sp-dw0h);
- ships.version last-write-wins clobbers when two operations write the same oscillating hull (sp-wa7c);
- orphaned cargo — hulls yanked mid-haul left holding unrelated goods;
- wasted round-trips, and reliance on FRAGILE MANUAL hull-dedication as a workaround.

Wants a proper hull-allocation architecture (a 'coordinator of coordinators') designed deliberately. NOT STARTED — this bead is the reminder to design it later. Related: sp-dw0h, sp-wa7c, sp-ubwi, sp-f5pr, sp-k1ka.

Admiral ask (2026-07-11 ~17:3xZ): send important metrics to the captain on every wake. BUILD: at wake-compose time the watchkeeper queries PG + prometheus (:9091) and prepends a ~10-line BRIEFING block to the wake prompt/mail. PROPOSED SET (captain rules the final cut — mail them the list): 
(1) TREASURY: balance now + net delta since last wake + net/hr last hour;
(2) EARNERS: active tour containers + heavy sells/hr last hour (the EarnerDark question answered preemptively);
(3) GUARDS since last wake: ceiling parks + supply parks + input-pauses (chain_input_pause_total delta) + chain kills (chain_pnl_kills_total delta) — the guard stack verdict counts;
(4) API: utilization %% (5m) + p95 limiter wait — burst-aware per the y0f6 lesson;
(5) FLEET POSTURE: laden/idle/stranded counts + any hull parked with a structured reason (no_reachable_source, stranded episodes);
(6) COVERAGE: stale-market count (>3h) / total — the scout program health number;
(7) INVENTORY VALUE: total + stored split (sp-7dlt queries reused Go-side) — the era-end rundown gauge;
(8) ALERTS: any prometheus alert currently firing (name only);
(9) ENGINEERING: deploys since last wake awaiting acceptance (from captain_events deploy markers if present, else omit).
DESIGN: one new watchkeeper briefing.go composing from existing readers (the detectors already hold PG + prometheus clients — reuse, no new pools); every line degrades to "n/a" on read error (a briefing failure must NEVER block a wake — fail open, log once); block capped ~600 chars; briefing_disabled escape (live by default per doctrine). Queries mirror validated dashboard SQL (financial.json panels are the source of truth for shapes). COLLISION: 6g96 is in watchkeeper territory (0A000 + event scoping) — build AFTER it gates or coordinate rebases. Deploy = watchkeeper rebuild+kickstart (zero fleet impact).
